replies.body: Woah, that's a big wall that doesn't tell me a whole lot.  I appreciate it though!  When you access the launcher, your network needs to get a pulse check with our patching service to make sure everything is up to date.  There might be a connection problem in this case preventing comms from being reached.  My suggestion in this case, in addition to your OSX update, would be to go over the steps in the [connection issues](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752664-Troubleshooting-Connection-Issues) guide.  Make sure to select Mac for instructions specific to your case.  Let me know if that helps!
I ended up getting the hextech repair tool and reinstalling.  I can launch the client now but the patcher says something went wrong around 60-70% so I'll keep on messing around.

The issue may specifically be with your connection, so reinstalling won't really solve this.  At this percent, you need a stable connection to grab updates from the patching servers or you'll get an error.  Make sure to go over the steps in the guide to help troubleshoot!
Thanks so much Porocles you were right.  I ended up adding League of Legends to programs that  can make changes to my computer and it patched and is now playable!
